{"word":"πλουτέω","slug":"πλουτέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>πλουτέω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πλοῦτος\">πλοῦτος</a></el>] ‘possess in abundance’, <b>be rich/wealthy<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ ref.\">ref.</a> to material assets <b><a href='B:490 1:53'>Lk 1:53</a>; <a href='B:610 6:9'>1 Ti 6:9</a>; <a href='B:730 18:3'>Rv 18:3</a>, <a href='B:730 18:15'>15</a>, <a href='B:730 18:19'>19</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> the status of God as owner and master of the universe <b><a href='B:520 10:12'>Ro 10:12</a></b> provides a transition to<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>c.</pp></b> in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ ref.\">ref.</a> to non-material assets <b><a href='B:490 12:21'>Lk 12:21</a>; <a href='B:530 4:8'>1 Co 4:8</a>; <a href='B:540 8:9'>2 Cor 8:9</a>; <a href='B:610 6:18'>1 Ti 6:18</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>d.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prob.\">prob.</a> in double sense of material and spiritual status <b><a href='B:730 3:17'>Rv 3:17f</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:πλουσίως\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:πλουτίζω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}